    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"Cultural Context"}],"depth":2,"type":"heading"},
    {"children":[{"type":"text","value":"下课 is a fundamental part of Chinese educational culture, marking the transition from formal\nlearning to break time. In Chinese schools, 下课 periods are important for student social\ninteraction and relaxation. The phrase 下课了 often brings relief and excitement to students,\nmarking freedom from classroom constraints and the beginning of social time or breaks."}],"type":"paragraph"}
